{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "We replaced the original detection head with a decoupling head and separated the classification task from the detection task because the original detection head shared the parameters of the two tasks of object localization and object classification, which would affect detection accuracy.",
    "Furthermore, we replaced the SPPF module with the SimSPPF module to achieve quicker inference speed and better feature representation ability.",
    "In the original YOLOv5 network, the C3 module is employed to reduce model complexity while increasing the receptive field.",
    "However, in low-light situations, the image's brightness and contrast are insufficient, and even noise is mixed, and the C3 module is unable to extract useful feature information and limit the influence of noise, which obviously impairs detection performance.",
    "In order to solve this problem, we designed a network inspired by C2f and SKNet 40, considering that low-frequency components often contain a large amount of semantic information in images and noise information often corresponds to high-frequency information."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In order to solve this problem, we designed a network inspired by C2f and SKNet 40, considering that low-frequency components often contain a large amount of semantic information in images and noise information often corresponds to high-frequency information."
  ]
